      "message": "\u003e Patch Set 7:\n\u003e \n\u003e (17 comments)\n\u003e \n\u003e Cool. And sorry for the delay on the review.\n\u003e \n\u003e macOS has “pthread introspection” hooks that receive notifications of certain thread events on-thread, including thread start. Mostly this is used as an interface for debuggers. But I don’t think the Linux world generally has anything that works exactly like that. As I recall, the hook that debuggers use on Linux to be notified of new thread creation runs on the parent thread, not the new thread. Worthless for this purpose.\n\nPTRACE_EVENT_CLONE could potentially function, but I think not as well. It\u0027d be more complicated to implement the hook from out-of-process and it\u0027s not composable with other things that want to use ptrace.",
